For instance , a lot of children nowadays replace their real life with the virtual world which computers create .
Another drawback is that in industry computers replace people 's labour , which leads to the increase of unemployment .
To conclude , I would like to say that the governments of all developed countries would n't have been so concerned about the so - called " problem 2000 " if the computer had not been so important to modern society .
Neuch.tel , 12th June 2001
